 {"id":"bd-65jkw","title":"casr: Add installation logic to install.sh","description":"Add CASR installation to install.sh in the Dicklesworthstone Stack phase (Phase 9).

Follow the pattern of other stack tools (ntm, dcg, ru, ubs). Steps:

1. Pre-check: command -v casr (skip if already installed)
2. Install using verified_installer mechanism:
   - fetch_and_run with checksum verification from checksums.yaml
   - CASR installer supports: --easy-mode, --version, --dest, --system, --yes,
     --verify, --from-source, --quiet, --no-gum, --no-verify, --no-configure,
     --no-skill, --offline, --force
   - Use: --easy-mode --quiet for non-interactive ACFS install
3. Verify installation:
   - command -v casr (binary exists)
   - casr --help | head -1 (responds correctly)
4. Post-install:
   - casr providers (detect which AI agents are available — don't fail if none yet)
   - Log installed version and detected providers
5. Error handling:
   - If install fails, log warning but don't fail the overall installer
   - casr is optional (useful but not critical)

IMPORTANT: Edit install.sh directly (hand-written production installer), NOT scripts/generated/.
