 {"id":"bd-67e19","title":"pcr: Add E2E installation test","description":"Add E2E test for post_compact_reminder.

Tests (with detailed logging):
1. Hook script installed: test -x ~/.local/bin/claude-post-compact-reminder
   → log file path, permissions, modification time
2. Hook registered in settings.json:
   python3 -c "import json; d=json.load(open(os.path.expanduser('~/.claude/settings.json'))); 
   hooks = d.get('hooks',{}).get('SessionStart',[]); 
   assert any('compact' in str(h) for h in hooks), 'PCR hook not found'"
   → log number of hooks found, PCR hook details
3. Hook script is valid bash: bash -n ~/.local/bin/claude-post-compact-reminder
   → assert exit 0
4. Settings.json backup exists: ls ~/.claude/settings.json.bak* (optional check)

Special handling:
- SKIP all tests if Claude Code is not installed (command -v claude)
- Log: "[SKIP] pcr: Claude Code not installed — PCR tests skipped"

Log format: [PASS/FAIL/SKIP] pcr: <test name> — <detail>

Exit codes:
- Exit 0 if all tests PASS or SKIP
- Exit 1 if any test FAILs
- Support --verbose flag for detailed output
